CLASS DESCRIPTION A Figure of Merit is a quantity used to characterize the performance of a device, system, or method relative to its alternatives. We use the figures of merit in this model to define the performance we are looking to quantify from a test step.

CLASS DESCRIPTION A test step is a single activity or action in a test protocol that a user will perform or a test administrator will perform. In the Human Factors and Usability model pattern we use a UML/Sysml activity element to document them.

The End User Package and Diagram is intended to be a database for each of the end users that will be used in Human Factors and Usability studies. The UML Actor type was extended to created the End User stereotype with specific tagged values used to collect and store the demographics of the subjects.
An End User Element should be created for each survey subject.
For each study participant add an end user to the package and diagram. Remember to fill in the demographic data stored in the tag values and the description in the elements notes
